<h2>Chapter 4: Statistical Inference</h2>

<h3>Sampling Methods</h3>
<p>Sampling selects representative data from a population.</p>

<h3>Confidence Intervals</h3>
<p>Confidence intervals estimate population parameters.</p>

<h3>Sample Size Determination</h3>
<p>Determines required data size for accuracy.</p>

<h3>Hypothesis Testing</h3>
<p>Used to make decisions using sample data.</p>

<h3>Z-test & t-test</h3>
<p>Statistical tests for population mean and proportion.</p>

